HEADWORD: Natrolite
<hw>Na"tro*lite</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Natron</ets> + <ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>natrolithe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A zeolite occurring
in groups of glassy acicular crystals, and in masses which often have a
radiated structure. It is a hydrous silicate of alumina and
soda.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Natron</ent>⟦br⟧
